<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf69710a2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s12306"><num value="12306">§ 12306.</num><heading> Safety certificates</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When a State is the authority issuing a number under this chapter, it may require that the individual in charge of a numbered vessel have a valid safety certificate issued under conditions set by the issuing authority, except when the vessel is subject to manning requirements under part F of this subtitle.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf69710a3-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/591">97 Stat. 591</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
